i M.A., Serafin M., Bratina A., Ukmar M., Pirko I., Johnson A.J., Furlan C., Pozzi-Mucelli R.S., Monti-Bragadin L., Grop A., Zambon M., Antonello R.M., Cazzato G., Zorzon M. Positivity of cytomegalovirus antibodies predicts a better clinical and radiological outcome in multiple sclerosis patients. <span><span class="ref-journal">Neurol. Res. </span>2006;<span class="ref-vol">28</span>:262\xe2\x80\x93269.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/16687051" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2647156&amp;issue-id=176961&amp;journal-id=556&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Neurol.+Res&amp;title=Positivity+of+cytomegalovirus+antibodies+predicts+a+better+clinical+and+radiological+outcome+in+multiple+sclerosis+patients&amp;author=R.+Zivadinov&amp;author=D.+Nasuelli&amp;author=M.A.+Tommasi&amp;author=M.+Serafin&amp;author=A.+Bratina&amp;volume=28&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;pages=262-269&amp;pmid=16687051&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2647156&amp;issue-id=176961&amp;journal-id=556&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="R115">115. <span class="citation">Fotheringham J., Jacobson S. Human herpesvirus 6 and multiple sclerosis potential mechanisms for virus-induced disease. <span><span class="ref-journal">Herpes. </span>2005;<span class="ref-vol">12</span>:4\xe2\x80\x939.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/16026638" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2647156&amp;issue-id=176961&amp;journal-id=556&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Herpes&amp;title=Human+herpesvirus+6+and+multiple+sclerosis+potential+mechanisms+for+virus-induced+disease&amp;author=J.+Fotheringham&amp;author=S+Jaco